post_cb({"44253024": {"ViewCount": "76", "Body": "<p>For example if I have:</p>\n<pre><code>float f = 3.3456;\nfloat g = 3.676455;\n\nint j = f;\nint k = g;\n</code></pre>\n<p>When the f,g are cast to int, will the behaviour be the same across all platforms ? Will j,k always be 3 ?</p>\n<p>For example, will k ever be 4 ?\nIs the fractional part always truncated, or is it ever rounded ?</p>\n<p>The reason this is slightly different from the question suggested as duplicate is that in this case the conversion is implicit. Please see the marked answer, as that directly contradicts the marked answer in the \"duplicate question\".</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "44253076", "Title": "When casting a float or double to an int, is behaviour consistent across platforms?", "CreationDate": "2017-05-30T03:38:18.883", "Id": "44253024", "CommentCount": "15", "FavoriteCount": "0", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditDate": "2017-05-30T04:11:23.440", "LastEditorUserId": "2990509", "LastActivityDate": "2017-05-30T04:56:19.420", "Score": "3", "OwnerUserId": "2990509", "Tags": "<c++>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_44253024_44253076_1": {"length": 20, "quality": 0.8695652173913043, "section_id": 37}}, "n3337": {"so_44253024_44253076_1": {"length": 20, "quality": 0.8695652173913043, "section_id": 34}}, "n4659": {"so_44253024_44253076_1": {"length": 21, "quality": 0.9130434782608695, "section_id": 37}}}, "44253076": {"Id": "44253076", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_44253024_44253076_0\">[...] will the behaviour be the same across all platforms ?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes. Yes it will.</p>\n<p>From <a href=\"http://wg21.link/n4659\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">N4659</a> (my emphasis in <strong>bold</strong>):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h2>7.10 Floating-integral conversions [conv.fpint]</h2>\n<p id=\"so_44253024_44253076_1\">(1) A prvalue of a floating-point type can be converted to a prvalue of an integer type. <strong>The conversion truncates</strong>; that is, <strong>the fractional part is discarded.</strong> <strong>The behavior is undefined</strong> if <strong>the truncated value cannot be represented in the destination type</strong>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "7881131", "LastActivityDate": "2017-05-30T04:19:07.777", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2017-05-30T03:46:39.780", "ParentId": "44253024", "CommentCount": "5", "OwnerUserId": "7881131", "LastEditDate": "2017-05-30T04:19:07.777"}});